Today I made a delicious and easy potato soup.

(great for those leftover Thanksgiving potatoes)

I cut up a few stalks of celery and broccoli and steamed them in water with some veggie bouillion.
After a few minutes of boiling I added a bag of frozen homestyle hash browns with red peppers. After all the veggies were soft I added 3 cups of leftover mashed potatoes and turned the heat down to low medium until they were mixed in and thickened the soup.  I added a few tablespoons of olive oil to make it more savory.  I turned the heat off completely and mixed in 2 cups of shredded cheddar cheese. SO EASY and SO GOOD!

Uploaded by:Artzyfartzy.

These origami boxes are made using the same size paper but vary in size by how they are folded. I love origami because its one of those crafts that require no tools or stinky glue/materials to create.

I have been really addicted to Youtube lately.  I found a hack to watch Youtube video in better quality.  If you put &fmt=18 after the address of the video it will play in better video and sound quality.  It really works.  I also know how to save videos or convert to MP3's ~~ but maybe I'll save that tidbit for another day.  :D These little tricks are really cool for converting for use on my Moto Q (which i Love love love ) ...
